# User Instruction Hard Lock

- Treat the user's wording as binding requirements. Do not reinterpret design/style asks.
- Re-read every user requirement line-by-line at least twice before editing, especially for design/style asks.
- For UI tasks, mirror requested fonts, sizes, colors, spacing, and layout exactly unless user asks for alternatives.
- Never make design/style "improvements" unless explicitly requested by the user.
- If any requirement is ambiguous, ask clarifying questions before editing code.
- Before implementation, restate acceptance criteria in concrete terms.
- For behavior/wiring tasks, validate root causes and verify edge cases twice before claiming done.
- For bug-fix and wiring tasks, test root cause hypotheses and confirmation paths twice before marking complete.
- Do not silently change font sizes/weights when user requested only container/spacing shrink.
- Do not change button or box widths unless user explicitly asked.
- For install/preview requests: follow `uninstall old -> install latest -> login -> capture evidence`.
- If automation captures wrong app/screen, explicitly say so and retry with corrected flow.
- Keep responses concise and factual; no speculative claims about verification.
